  name: 1,
  title: 'When the Party Never Stops: 5 Ways to Attain Awesome Startup Culture',
  article: '<p>At a San Francisco office overlooking the Transamerica building, the CEO of LoungeBuddy is pushing an original airplane bar cart and is graciously pouring cocktails for his team. It is 6:30pm on a Thursday and it is officially Happy Hour. The atmosphere in the office is jovial and positive. Why wouldn&rsquo;t it be? LoungeBuddy recently raised a $3M Series A round and launched their app on the Apple watch.</p><p>Founded to give travelers access to the best airport lounges around the world, LoungeBuddy is a company that was built around fun. Since it seems that they have figured out the secret to happy employees, I wanted to find out exactly what makes their company culture so great. I started the interview with one of LoungeBuddy&rsquo;s founders, Brent Griffith, with preconceived beliefs about the startup culture, but was surprised by the things I learned. </p><p>1. Hiring Is Critical I started off the interview by asking about the parties and trips that LoungeBuddy organizes for its employees, but the conversation was promptly steered to LoungeBuddy&rsquo;s most important aspect of culture. It turns out that the key to building an amazing culture, is to hire people that fit perfectly into your organization. &ldquo;If you don&rsquo;t find people that are dedicated, smart and passionate about what you are doing, if those interests are not aligned then it will not support a culture that you are trying to build,&rdquo; Brent states. The word &ldquo;passion&rdquo; was used countless times during my interview because it is, in fact, passion that builds that contagious enthusiasm which spreads to anyone that comes in contact with the company.</p><p>2. Cash Is King, or Is It? LoungeBuddy also has an answer for the complex question of structuring compensation. In order to align everyone&rsquo;s incentives they typically give multiple options (equity vs. cash compensation) to new hires. They prefer that everyone in the company has some equity. Flexible hours are also important in the tech world. LoungeBuddy employees typically start around 10 am to 11am and some engineers will stay until 3am. There have been internal discussion on acquiring a cot for those who just can&rsquo;t let go of their code. The proposal was vetoed to avoid burnout and preserve a fun working environment.</p><p>3. Keep the Party Going Ok, we finally got to the part that I wanted to hear about, the parties! Two of the founders met organizing events in Las Vegas for an electronics show. The third founder they met at one of their parties. So, to say that these people know how to have fun, would be an understatement. Previously working at The VAULT, a coworking space, the team had access to all of the events planned by the space. The happy hours, lunch demos and VAULT organized trips were a great way to bond with the team. Today, having their own office, the founders handle event planning on their own.</p><p>Brent told me about their recent company retreat to Puerto Vallarta. The team worked really hard for 6 to 12 months, hit a number of milestones and accomplished a great deal. Employees were told to pack for a certain climate and to show up at the airport. At their arrival, the secret retreat location was revealed. The trip was very cost effective and it presented a great opportunity to bond outside of the office. In the last six months, founders have organized other team events such as sailing on the bay, SF Giants games, the symphony, an African dinner and miniature golf outing.</p><p>4. What Really Makes Us Tick A huge motivator for most of us is growth. That&rsquo;s why LoungeBuddy cross-trains the members and helps them improve their skills. They make sure to give people opportunities to develop themselves and get exposure to the different areas of the company. &ldquo;Showing that you care and putting effort into helping other people to improve is key&rdquo; says Brent. Also, keeping the organization flat allows people to have a voice and reduce uncertainty through transparency.</p><p>5. Lose the Battle, Win the War Studies show that the number one reason for startup failure is disagreement between founders. When asked how the three serial entrepreneurs handle the challenge, Brent states: &ldquo;We have done a good job respecting each other&rsquo;s opinions&#8230; Because we are aligned to find the best solution, we work toward a creative way of addressing problems.&rdquo;</p><p>So, there you have it. The key to a successful company is building a culture that is driven by passion, growth, respect, goal alignment and, most importantly, fun. This approach has clearly paid off as the company has experienced great success in not only raising funds but gaining traction. LoungeBuddy is currently growing and is hiring engineering talent.</p>'
}, {
  id: 2,
  title: 'What is LoungeBuddy?',
  article: '<p>LoungeBuddy is an airport lounge booking platform that allows you to reserve access into airport lounges regardless of your elite status, lounge memberships, or class of service. We do not own or operate any of the lounges on our platform. View locations available around the world from our lounge partners. We are continuously adding new lounges for you to access. </p><p>If you have complimentary access into a lounge based on a credit card or your ticket class you can download the free LoungeBuddy app to find lounges you have access to. In addition to discovering what lounges you can access for free with your access methods, you can also book access into the lounges from the LoungeBuddy app.</p>'
}, {
  id: 3,
  title: 'American Express To Acquire LoungeBuddy',
  article: '<p>American Express (NYSE: AXP) today announced it will acquire LoungeBuddy, a digital platform that enables travelers to discover, book and access airport lounges worldwide. Founded in 2013, LoungeBuddy&rsquo;s mobile app and website (www.loungebuddy.com) provide a premium airport experience with robust lounge ratings and reviews, comprehensive eligibility criteria, and global airport coverage through its lounge partners. The acquisition is expected to be completed in April 2019.</p><p>&ldquo;The expansive airport lounge access we offer our premium Card Members through the Global Lounge Collection is among the most popular travel benefits we offer, which is why we continue to invest in enhancing the lounge access and services we provide,&rdquo; said Chris Cracchiolo, Senior Vice President, Global Loyalty and Benefits, American Express. &ldquo;With the acquisition of LoungeBuddy, we will be able to leverage its cutting-edge platform to develop additional ways to become an essential part of our Card Members&rsquo; digital lives.&rdquo;</p><p>American Express has been partnering with LoungeBuddy since 2017 to provide information in the American Express mobile app for the more than 1,200 airport lounges that Platinum Card and Centurion Members can access through the American Express Global Lounge Collection.</p><p>&quot;Since the beginning of our partnership with American Express, it was clear that American Express shared the same commitment to elevate their customers&rsquo; entire travel experience and beyond,&quot; said Tyler Dikman, Co-Founder and CEO, LoungeBuddy. &quot;As a company rooted in providing a highly premium experience using innovative technologies, we are excited to work even more closely with American Express to further deliver on this for their Card Members across the globe,&quot; added Zac Altman, Co-Founder and CTO, LoungeBuddy.</p><p>After the acquisition, LoungeBuddy will operate as a wholly-owned subsidiary of American Express under the leadership of its original founders and will continue to develop its technologies and capabilities in digital travel services.</p><p>Update as of April 1, 2019: Today, American Express closed the acquisition of LoungeBuddy. Moving forward, lounge booking services through the LoungeBuddy platform will be exclusively available for American Express Card Members. Additionally, while there are some changes to the number of lounges available to book through the LoungeBuddy platform, American Express is actively working with a number of lounge operators to expand the options available for Card Members to book through the platform in the near future. The acquisition has no impact on the lounge access provided to Platinum and Centurion Card Members through the American Express Global Lounge Collection. </p><p>Information Related to Forward-Looking Statements</p><p>This release includes forward-looking statements that reflect management&rsquo;s expectations about future events, including expectations regarding the transaction. These forward-looking statements are subject to risks and uncertainties. The words &ldquo;expect,&rdquo; &ldquo;intend,&rdquo; &ldquo;plan,&rdquo; &ldquo;will,&rdquo; &ldquo;may,&rdquo; &ldquo;should,&rdquo; &ldquo;could,&rdquo; &ldquo;would,&rdquo; and similar expressions are intended to identify forward-looking statements. Readers are cautioned not to place undue reliance on these forward-looking statements, which speak only as of the date on which they are made. American Express undertakes no obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statements. Factors that could cause actual results to differ materially from these forward-looking statements include, but are not limited to, the parties&rsquo; ability to satisfy the closing conditions, the underlying assumptions related to the transaction proving to be inaccurate or unrealized, and the company&rsquo;s ability to integrate LoungeBuddy and leverage its platform and lounge network. A further description of these and other risks and uncertainties can be found in American Express&rsquo; Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2018 and its other reports filed with the SEC.</p>'
}];

